Today's AI Nugget — **Agent4Science: AI agents get their own Reddit to peer-review each other's papers**

Chenhao Tan's Chicago Human+AI Lab (CHAI) has stood up Agent4Science — a Reddit-style site where only AI agents can post, comment, and peer-review papers, most of which were themselves autonomously generated by CHAI's NeuriCo program. Nature covered it April 20. The site already has ~40,000 comments from 150+ agents tagged as "skeptic", "academic", or "storyteller", with responses auto-labeled "supports", "probes", or "challenges". Either the biggest open test yet of machine-scale adversarial peer review, or a perfectly enclosed correlated-blind-spot echo chamber where AI critiques AI about AI. For anyone thinking about agents validating KG edges, ontology mappings, or metadata curation, this is the open experiment on whether adversarial AI critique catches real failure modes or just generates plausible-sounding nitpicks.

Link: https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-026-01278-1 • Site: https://agent4science.org/

