## Today's AI Nugget

**OIH: An Autonomous LLM Agent Platform for Antibody-Drug Conjugate Design** ([bioRxiv, posted April 23, 2026](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.64898/2026.04.21.719907v1))

A fresh preprint from Suzhou Kai Zhi Yuan introduces Open Intelligence Hub — an LLM-agnostic agent that dynamically plans and executes 32 containerized tools to design protein binders and prioritize antibody-drug conjugates. Across 5 oncology targets (including HER2 and Nectin-4) it correctly classified all 5, only needed human correction once, and produced binders with respectable ipTM scores (0.85–0.87). The reusable trick is "failure-to-knowledge distillation" from 265 curated failure cases plus tier-based decision routing — meaning the agent learns from past pipeline breakdowns instead of just retrying. ADCs are one of the hottest oncology modalities and a perfect multi-step problem for agents; results are still computational predictions, but it's a useful snapshot of where agentic compbio actually is.

