**Run summary — biomedical-agentic-ai 2026-05-26**

**Pick:** SpatialClaw — memory-augmented autonomous agent ecosystem for spatial omics analysis. Group at Northwestern Polytechnical University (Xuequn Shang corresponding). bioRxiv DOI 10.64898/2026.05.21.723451 v1, posted 2026-05-25. Thirty specialized spatial-omics skills plus a graph-based persistent memory architecture with three hierarchical layers (session/episodic/semantic) under a deterministic promotion policy, bridged to the main agent via a Memory-Augmented Reasoning (MAR) operator. Beats both standard-LLM and memory-only configurations across three memory-sensitive scenarios on ten skills. End-to-end TNBC tumor-microenvironment analysis on a 15-section cohort in three conversational turns with zero direct scripting. Read: versioned-nodes-and-edges memory is essentially a knowledge-graph substrate for agent state — directly in Su Lab's wheelhouse on agentic AI, biomedical KGs, and reproducibility.

**Candidate funnel (last 2 days, 2026-05-25..2026-05-26):**

- bioRxiv (full collection paged across 6 cursors, 168 items, 28 keyword hits) — survivors after discarding spurious matches:
  - **SpatialClaw** (10.64898/2026.05.21.723451 v1, 2026-05-25) — **chosen**
  - Carbon: Decoding the Language of Life (10.64898/2026.05.22.727119 v1, 2026-05-25, Hugging Face / Bernardo) — strong genomic foundation model paper (3B/8B decoder-only, non-overlapping 6-mer tokenization, 65K-131K context, competitive with Evo2-7B at <half params and tens-fold faster inference) but architecturally a foundation-model story not agentic; close runner-up on quality, weaker on brief fit
  - OryzaG3 single-species rice pangenome foundation model (10.64898/2026.05.22.727045 v1, 2026-05-26) — foundation-model not agentic, plant-focused (less biomedical fit)
- arXiv (500 cached entries, 94 biomedical × agentic-keyword matches in 2-day window):
  - What Makes a Medical Checker Trainable? (2605.25988 v1, 2026-05-25, Yuelyu Ji) — diagnostic study of NLI checkers as process rewards in GRPO-trained medical RAG; signal-collapse and reward-hacking findings are technically interesting but contribution is diagnostic rather than architectural
  - Uncertainty Reasoning with LLMs for Explainable Disease Diagnosis (2605.25566 v1, 2026-05-25) — on-theme but architecturally less novel
  - A Multimodal 3D Foundation Model for Light Sheet Fluorescence Microscopy (2605.26026 v1, 2026-05-25) — biomedical foundation model, narrow modality
