**Today's pick:** LinkD / LinkD-Agent — Kuan-lin Huang's group at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai, bioRxiv 10.64898/2026.04.19.719462 v2 posted 2026-06-07. Four-layer agentic drug-repurposing platform: LinkD-Bind diffusion-based binding affinity (ranks first in 8 of 9 BindingDB / Davis / KIBA benchmarks with the biggest gains under cold-start), LinkD-Select selectivity-plus-docking (95.3% recovery of known drug-target pairs), LinkD-Pheno phenotypic integration across 960 cancer cell lines (34 novel drug-gene pairs, ~85% recovery of known targets in top 50), and a natural-language LinkD-Agent orchestrator on top, served as a public web platform. Population-scale validation across 11.5M individuals (Mount Sinai EHR + UK Biobank) shows LinkD-prioritized propranolol (HR 0.82) and carvedilol (HR 0.92) reduce 5-year prostate cancer incidence vs metoprolol — corroborated by ADRB2 docking and LNCaP wet-lab growth inhibition. Same Huang lab as the May 5 ADA Consortium agent-as-auditor paper, now moving to agent-as-multi-scale-repurposing-orchestrator.

